  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the wood-fired oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Cut the peppers in half and remove the seeds and membranes.",
    "In a large bowl, mix together the olive oil, onion, garlic, paprika, salt, and pepper.",
    "Place the peppers in a comal or large baking dish and brush with the oil mixture.",
    "Cover the comal with foil and bake for 30 minutes.",
    "Remove the foil and top each pepper with vegan mozzarella cheese and breadcrumbs.",
    "Return to the oven and bake for an additional 15 minutes, or until the cheese is melted and bubbly.",
    "Garnish with chopped parsley.",
    "Serve hot and enjoy!",
    "Let the peppers cool slightly before serving.",
    "If desired, serve with a side of your favorite dipping sauce.",
    "Store any leftovers in an airtight container in the refrigerator for up to 3 days."
  ],
